title: Salah ud Din Junejo wins NA-210 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarian candidate Salah Ud Din Junejo has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-210 Sanghar-II by securing 1,50,195 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Grand Democratic Alliance candidate Saira Bano, who bagged 108,194 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 47.08 percent.
